# gitone

**To initialize git -**
git init

**To get files from github - **
git clone https://github.com/MaynulIslam/gitone.git

**After edit any file, to check the status -**
git status

**To make all the files in the stage from working directory -**
git add --all

**To make everything again in working directory from stage -**
git reset
git reset --hard

**To delete a file -** 
git rm two.txt

**To delete the file forcefully -**
git rm two.txt -f

**when everything in stage then commit(local repository) -**
git commit -m "**Write here about the changes in files**"

**To go back from commit - **
git reset HEAD~

**to show the branched in git -** 
git branch

**to add a new branch- **
git branch new branch

**to switched to another branch -** 
git checkout new branch

**to marge two branches -**
git merge branch name

t**o make everything in remote(github) -**
git push origin

**to push new branches in remote -**
git push origin branchName

**to get updated data from remote -**
git fetch

**then, to see the remote changes - **
git merge

**to pull branch data from remote - **
git pull

**git pull means (fetch + merge)**
